title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>For any positive integers <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>, we have the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m\times  n]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Zero Matrix</html:dfn> to be the matrix whose components are all zero. We denote this by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {0}]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[0]]></fr:tex> because it will play the analogous counterpart that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[0\in \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> plays.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
