addr="alex-nelson"
title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We call an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m\times  n]]></fr:tex> matrix <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}=(a_{i,j})]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Upper Triangular</html:dfn> if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a_{i,j}=0]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i>j]]></fr:tex>, e.g., when <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m=n]]></fr:tex> it looks like: <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A} = \begin {bmatrix}     a_{1,1} & a_{1,2} & a_{1,3} & … & a_{1,n}\\     0      & a_{2,2} & a_{2,3} & … & a_{2,n}\\     0      & 0       & a_{3,3} & … & a_{3,n}\\     \vdots  & \vdots  & \vdots  & \ddots  & \vdots \\     0      & 0      & 0      & …  & a_{n,n}   \end {bmatrix}]]></fr:tex></fr:p><fr:p>Furthermore, if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a_{i,i}=0]]></fr:tex>, then we call <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn
